# .swanlake-no-beacon -- example opt-out marker (NOT active by default).
#
# To activate: rename this file to `.swanlake-no-beacon` (drop the .example
# suffix). Once active, the file excludes this directory and every
# descendant from `swanlake beacon sweep`, `swanlake beacon deploy`,
# `swanlake scan`, and the SessionStart nudge hook.
#
# Two flavors:
#
#   1. Empty file -- exclude everything below this directory.
#   2. YAML frontmatter `surfaces: [<id>, <id>]` -- exclude only the
#      listed surface-ids in this subtree.
#
# Example for the surface-list flavor:
#
#     surfaces: [cms-scratch-foo, cms-scratch-bar]
#
# See docs/swanlake-no-beacon.md in the swanlake repo for full
# semantics.
